external_knowledge:
- "seafarers" metaphorically refers to the carriers; 
- "ocean of skies" metaphorically refers to the flight operations; 
- "more than 500 times" refers to the condition of total_flights > 500; 
- "burning through more than a million gallons of fuel" refers to the condition of total_fuel_consumption > 1000000; 
- "each sip" metaphorically refers to the average fuel consumption per flight.

sql:
SELECT flight_number
FROM flights
WHERE arr_delay > (SELECT AVG(arr_delay) FROM flights);

SELECT carrier_name
FROM carriers
WHERE carrier_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Significantly delayed: flight delays greater than 30 minutes;
Departure points: origin airport codes;
Arrival points: destination airport codes;
How late: delay time in minutes.

sql:
SELECT flight_id, delay_type, delay_minutes, delay_reason, delay_category
FROM flight_delays
WHERE delay_minutes > 30;

external_knowledge:
- "bustling hubs" refers to airports with high flight activity;
- "vitality" is a metaphor indicating the level of activity and engagement in terms of flights and user access;
- The SQL query ranks airports by first ordering by total flights and then by total users, both in descending order.

sql:
SELECT airport_name
FROM airports
WHERE airport_id = 1;

SELECT carrier_id, AVG(arr_delay) AS Average_Arrival_Delay
FROM flights
GROUP BY carrier_id;
